name: University of Chicago, Regenstein Library
directions: The bathrooms on the second through fifth floors each have a separate, single-user, locking, gender-free bathroom, in addition to multi-user men's and ladies' rooms.
comment: Requires U of C student ID or library day pass.

name: Tamarind Bay
directions: Tamarind Bay is in the basement, down the stairs. It is an Indian restaurant, and the bathroom is for customers.
comment: There are two non-gendered bathrooms. One says "Tiny bathroom" and "Not so tiny bathroom." They were clean when I went there.

name: Gladstone Hotel
directions: Walk through the front doors, go towards the elevator in the lobby, just past it on the right is a single genderfree washroom. Also in between the Melody Bar and the Art Bar is another genderfree single stall, as well as a genderfree washroom with two separate stalls inside.For an accessible washroom go up the ramp and into the Melody Bar, through the bar and take a left to get into the lobby. The single stall washroom there is accessible.
comment: Always open. If it's the middle of the night  the front desk person will probably want to know what you're doing there.

name: Pacific Spirit Communtiy Health Centre
directions: It's a wheel-chair accessible, gender-neutral washroom on the main floor.  Walk straight in the doors.  An elevator will be right in front of you & reception is on the right.  Go down the hallway between reception & the elevator & the washrooms are right there.
comment: open during office hours (8:30-4:30 ish)

name: Harvest Co-Op, Central Square
directions: Just past the cafe, on the left.
comment: Gotta get the key from the desk.

name: Camden County College
directions: These bathrooms (there are two!) are on the 2nd floor in the Helene Fuld(sp?), which is the building next to CIM. You will find them at the top of the stairs on your left.
comment: Don't worry that Helene Fuld is the primary building for nursing students. Just walk in, and it shouldn't be a problem. Many students take biology classes there anyhow!

name: People's Cafe
directions: ground floor, in the back

name: Missouri Lounge
directions: First floor, in the back
comment: Cool bar, open 'til 2 am

name: Le Baobab
directions: Rear of the restaurant.
comment: One single-stall locking bathroom. This cafe serves fair-trade coffee and sells it in bulk (for cheaper than the supermarket) and offers free Wifi. Corner of 3e Avenue and rue Wellington in Verdun. De L'Eglise metro.

name: Al Taib
street: on guy just south of ste.catherine on the east side of the street,
directions: one of 3 locations of al taib downtown at concordia - best for washroom facilities - southeast side of guy almost right on corner of guy+ste catherine
comment: small single genderfree washroom to the right of the till, really clean, nice, people friendly, and you have to buy a water and that's it (sometimes you can go in and use it if it's busy, like during lunch)

name: Belgo Building
directions: some of the washrooms on some of the floors of the building are handicap, some are so empty and relaxed it seems like anyone can walk in - there are a few that say things like "women" and aren't single stalled, but the signs are painted over so much it feels like they're probably for whoever. go into the main entrance and either up the stairs in front of you, or to the left to get to the elevators
comment: good bet if you're in that area of downtown - often open, good hours-chill arts gallery building, people are relaxed and don't pay any attention to each other, really

name: 2110 Concordia Centre for Gender Advocacy
directions: right next to le frigo vertwalk into 2110 mackay, there's a hallway and 2 doors, one on the left one on the right - the one on the left is the 2110 (there are signs everywhere) - totally 100% accessible, everyone welcome, you can come just to use the washroom, too
comment: open mon-thursday 12-5 and 12-6pm....ofen open a wee later for events

name: la croissointerie
street: ste catherine west of guy about 6 blocks - (sorry, i can't find the exact address online) on the north side of the street, cafe with green awning
comment: there are 2 washrooms, both gendered, at the back, but its very discreet, quiet and single bathrooms. i've never had problems using either the mens or womens. the cafe itself is usually busy with students, so if you go in acting like you're looking for someone, or just act casually, and go all the way to the back, it's never a problem. the people that work there are really relaxed and friendly, too.

name: Subway Sandwiches
directions: enter on sutter st at polk. go left. single stall gender neutral and accessible!

name: Concordia University, EV Complex
directions: Every floor. The one on the first floor is across from the lobby, down the hall a bit from the security desk.

name: University of San Diego
directions: All the buildings have restrooms that get cleaned everyday.
comment: When you drive in ask for a visitor pass.

Hello. We are in process of renovating a gorgeous 1920 building into an Art Lounge here in St. Petersburg and our plan is to create a single 'bathroom' where every stall has a toilet which is enclosed in it's own small room. Complete privacy for everyone.  Then everyone shares the 4 sinks and "primping" area.  This will be a classy modern art gallery mashed together with a swanky lounge. I've seen this type of bath setup all over Europe and am going to use it here.  But the city is giving me a headache about it.  Can you please offer any advice or comments to help us along?  Much thanks and good luck to us all!  Michael  :-)lrn2thnk@tampabay.rr.com

name: Earlham College
directions: Landrum Bolling Center (First building on the right if you enter on the main drive).  The bathroom is a locking, single-stall multi-gender accessible bathroom.
comment: Only open from 8AM to 11PM on school days- less on weekends.  There are other bathrooms on campus (try Lilly library, where there is a locking single stall if you walk down the hall past the left of the main desk). All in all, Earlham is a safe space for transfolks.

name: Value Village
directions: Ask for key at front desk, bathroom is on the right from the entrance.
comment: I don't know *how* accessible this makes it, but it's the largest single-toilet bathroom I've ever seen in my life - roomy and spacious, could be a bedroom. Open til 9 most days? 6 or 7 on Sundays.

name: park place stadium 16
directions: down hall across from the concession stand before you hand your ticket in for the movie. It is a family restroom.

name: Grubsteak
directions: inside the resturant grubsteak, next to tattoo shop
comment: open till 4 am!!

directions: inside the resturant grubsteak, next to tattoo shop
comment: two genderfree bathrooms, for customers only,but the guys there are nice and i bet they wouldn't mind if you used it, puls it gets busy and i think not alot of them would even know.

name: Gainesville, GA / Belk (Housewares Dept) inside Lakeshore Mall
directions: There are 2 Belks in this mall... you are looking for the one with the men's, kid's, and housewares.  The restroom is located in an area near the bedding.  There are also traditional bathrooms, but there is 1 unisex/handicap bathroom with its own door and lock.

name: Norman Mayer Branch - New Orleans Public Library
directions: 2nd Floor, near the non-fiction section. Its the only restroom on the second floor. Ask for the key at the 2nd floor information desk.
comment: There is an elevator.Hours are: 10 am - 7 pm, Mon. - Thurs.10 am - 5 pm, Sat.504-596-3100For more information (or to check if anything has changed):http://neworleanspubliclibrary.org/~nopl/info/branches/branches.htm

name: Fred Meyer
directions: Right off of the Cornelius Pass Rd exit of Highway 26. Gender neutral bathroom in between M and F bathrooms, near pharmacy.
comment: Hours: 7am to 11pm 7 days a week

name: B‰tô Thai
directions: Left-hand side of the restaurant, just beyond the central desk/bar
comment: Two gendered single bathrooms. A wall in front of the doors to the bathroom affords a bit of privacy as to which bathroom you chose. Thai restaurant in the Village. Ste-Catherine and de la Visitation, Beaudry metro.

name: M Bar
directions: On the first floor in the hallway between the main bar room and the VIP section.

name: Leunigs
directions: Two single seater bathrooms for any gender

name: Kohls (U-Mall)
directions: Back by the customer service desk there are three doors to bathrooms- one to a womens room, one to a mens room, and one to a single seater for either gender and wheelchair accessible

name: La Popessa
directions: end of the front counter
comment: Three single stalls, men's women's and disabled (non-gendered). Pasta restaurant on the south side of the Palais des Congrès, corner of Saint-Antoine and Côte de la Place-d'Armes, in Old Montreal (Place-d'Armes metro).

name: Mall of NH
directions: near Best Buy, and near Spencer's Gift's, follow signs
comment: Mall hours 8:30 to 9:30 pm mon-satsun - 11-6pmShopping hours 10:00 am to 9:30 pm mon-sat11-6pm

name: Madoka Restaurant/Bainbridge Island, WA
directions: first floor, back around the bar, 2 ungendered locking restrooms
comment: our favorite restaurant

name: factory direct home furnishings
directions: In the back, just tell the staff that nature calls.
comment: Eclectic, laid back furniture store since 1901.

name: I Got Cha Pizza
directions: If you enter from the take-out entrance, turn to your right. From the bar entrance, turn left. The 2 gender neutral, single stall bathrooms are on the hallway between entrances.
comment: Mon-Wed 4 pm - 10 pmThu-Fri 4 pm - 3:30 amSat 11 am - 3:30 amSun 11 am - 8 pm(714) 680-5400http://www.facebook.com/pages/I-Got-Cha-Pizza/256058709069

name: Resto du Village
directions: Adjacent to the counter, on your right facing the register
comment: A Gay Village mainstay offering traditional Quebec meals and diner fare. Open 24 hours a day. On Wolfe just below Ste-Catherine. Metro Beaudry.

name: Coffee House Cafe
comment: Great place to hang out.

name: Rancho's
directions: in the rear of the place there are two single gendered stalls.
comment: great vegan/veggie food!

name: San Diego International Airport
directions: by the security checkpoint, entrance to the southwest airlines terminal there is a family bathroom between two traditionally gendered options
comment: this bathroom is outside of the gate/security area. there only appear to be gendered options within the terminal itself!

name: Oakland Airport
directions: by gate 26,27,28, in the southwest area. a family bathroom next to two gendered bathrooms.
comment: you'll need to be flying to use this as it is within the terminal.

name: Pokez
directions: in the saloon doors through the kitchen. two single stall gendered bathrooms.
comment: punk rock and amazing vegan burritos. give this place a try, they probably won't bug you about the bathroom.

name: Lucky Buck's
directions: visible from the street, single stall gender neutral and accessible.

name: T-Deli
directions: straight in, visible from the street. single stall gender neutral accessible bathroom.

name: Urban Grind
directions: there are two bathrooms, labeled bathroom 1 and bathroom 2.
comment: not sure if bathrooms are accessible. bathroom one has a one way mirror, so it's kinda freaky

name: NewBreak Coffee
directions: in the back.
comment: it's token operated, so you have to buy something to get a token. the place has a great tea selection!

name: Toi, Moi et Café
directions: Rear of the restaurant.
comment: Ritzy coffee shop/restaurant at Notre-Dame and Rue de Lévis, one block east of Atwater, in Little Burgundy; Lionel-Groulx metro. Fair-trade coffee available.

name: Adagio Cafe
comment: Super nice and clean!

name: Cole Coffee
directions: The coffee shop is on the corner and has two entrances -enter from the 63rd street entrance and the door to the bathroom is dead ahead.
comment: If it is locked, the key is on the metal frame of a french press on the counter.  The coffee is somewhere between freebasing and rocket fuel if you want to take it for a spin ;-)

name: Leather Bound
street: 96 Front Street (near corner of Front & Main)
directions: Downstairs. You have to ask for the key.
comment: I don't remember whether it's gendered or not, but Leather Bound caters to transwomen and crossdressers and is a friendly and safe place.

name: Collegetown Bagels
directions: Go all the way to the back of the restaurant, follow the narrow hallway on the right hand side, back even farther.
comment: Open Mon-Sat, 7am-7:30pm; Sun, 7am-5pm. Bathrooms are small but private. They don't care if you buy anything or just come in to pee.

name: Taylor's Mini Mart
directions: Straight back from the door.
comment: Right off the Richmondville exit of I-88

name: Hess Express
directions: Straight back from the door.
comment: Open till 11pm?

name: Elting Memorial Library
directions: It's right when you walk in. Before you even get into the library part.

name: Polyclinique Medicale Concorde
street: 300 de la Concorde East Blvd. H7G 2E6
directions: There is at least one restroom on each floor.
comment: I don't know the opening hours.

name: Laval's Multiculturelle Public Library
street: 1535 Chomedey Blvd. (Between St. Martin and Souvenir blvd.)
directions: There are two restroom, one upstairs and the other one on the main floor.
comment: Usually open from noon to 9:00 pm.Because it's a municipal building, the opening hours are kinna weird!

name: A1 Pizzeria
directions: This is a family restaurant and bar. Bathrooms are for customers, but they'll probably let you use it if you ask nicely. Come in the front door, go to the left past the desk and to the back of the room. Go through the door marked for bathrooms and there's a men's room, a women's room and a unisex handicap room. All three are single rooms with toilet, sink and locking door.

name: Stiehl's Body Modification Station
street: 120 South Cayuga Street (South end of the Commons)
directions: Bathroom is supposed to be for customers, but the proprietors and employees are great people who are used to freaks and gender outlaws and will probably let you use the bathroom anyway if you come in and ask nicely.
comment: Monday - Noon - 6:00 pmTuesday thru Saturday - Noon - 8:00pm

name: P&C
directions: Go in the main door, the bathrooms are to the left near the service desk. They are gendered, but no one ever seems to watch them or care who's in them. Two large rooms with toilet, sink, handrail and locking door.
comment: Open 24 hours. Generally fairly clean.

name: Valero Station
directions: This is a gas station/convenience store across the street from a big cinema complex. There's one bathroom, gender free, a door that locks, a sink and a toilet. Walk in the front door, the bathroom's pretty much straight ahead at the back of the store.

name: Cherry Bean Gourmet Coffeehouse
directions: In the back of the coffeehouse.
comment: This is a cool, queer friendly place. You need to get a token from someone at the register to use the locking, single stall restroom.

name: Harris Teeter Supermarket (24 Hours)
directions: Follow signs in produce section, to the right of the store.
comment: open 24/7 & Clean.

name: Harris Teeter Supermarket (24 hours)
directions: Go tru doors in fresh produce section.
comment: Open 24/7  Store in Mt Pleasant is good also.

name: Pan American Pancake House
directions: Across from Big Lots on south end of beach. Restrooms are in rear, inside. Just ask Connie, or anyone really, if OK.
comment: This restaurant has always been Very GLBT FRIENDLY for the last 20 years.It's where people go for a late, afterhours bite.The person that would make a negative comment towards you here,would be the one at risk. It's pretty informal, esp. at night. Be sure and say hello to dear Connie when you're there.

name: Time Out (Gay Bar)
street: Main and Oak Streets, Downtowne Myrtle Beach
directions: Near 8th Ave North and Hwy 17 Bus. Across Broadway Ave from Macfadden Music store.DO NOT PARK BEHIND BAR,you WILL be towed. Park out front or on street side of bar.
comment: Oldest Gay Bar in Myrtle Beach. Usually open from about 4pm till 2-3am. Door person will usually let you in use the restroom, depending how busy they are and if you don't look like a "street person".

name: Dillards
street: Coastal Grand Mall,  Hwy 17 By-pass and Hwy 501
directions: Upstairs on 2nd floor. Straight out from up escalators.  Single stall and private
comment: Regular store hours till 9pm.

name: Bi-Lo  24 Hour Grocery
street: 38th Ave North and Hwy 17 Bypass;  Plantation Point Shop Cent.
directions: Upon entering go to Right. Single stall bathrooms are in the Deli deptment, which is unmanned at night.
comment: Most Krogers and other Bi-los in area have similar setup.

name: Kroger (open 24 hours)
directions: Upon entering store, go to left. Restrooms are in Deli, behind seating area.
comment: Kroger in Garden City Beach is similar. Also, most Bi-Lo grocery stores here, have single stale bathrooms in their Deli depts. All here are open 24 hours with the deli's unmanned at night.

name: BP Kangeroo (24 hours)
street: Corner of Hwy 17 Bus. and 6th Ave South
directions: Kangeroo is in front of NMB Post Office. Restrooms on left as you enter.

name: The Center Project (GLBT)
directions: Near intersection of 3rd Ave South. Look for rainbow flag in Hewitt Plaza strip mall. Be sure and pick up information on T-Time gender forum the 1st Saturday of every month, 7-9pm.

name: Micheal's Gelato
directions: Back right corner of store.
comment: It wasn't the cleanest bathroom, but useable. If you visit, sit upstairs on the balcony.

name: Kit Kat Klub
directions: In the back of the restaurant
comment: It is a martini bar that is 'T' friendly. Good food too!!

name: Old Mission San Jose
directions: Enter gift shop, go three doorways down and turn left.
comment: Two single-room restrooms, not labled for gender. 10am-5pm daily. Admission fee for museum is $3 for adults and $1 for students, but often you can get to the restroom without paying this if you ask the cashier.

name: Laughing Planet Cafe
directions: At the back; you have to fetch the key at the front counter

name: Good Foods Co-Op
comment: Freshly renovated. There are no gender-direction signs on the doors (2 single stall rooms) but they might have just not been put up yet. My mom thought it was weird but I say it's neat.

name: Dagwood's Deli & Sub Shop
directions: To the left of the counter
comment: One of the few places I've seen that has two single-toilet locking bathrooms that aren't gender labeled.

name: Simmons College Library
directions: Once you find the library building, head upstairs to the library proper. There are two bathrooms, both single stall. One is designated female, and the other is for everyone with a need to pee.
comment: These bathrooms are in a college, so after 5 you need an ID to get in the building.

name: Union Jack's
street: Northshore Dr. just south of Kingston Pk.
directions: 'ladies'' is straight ahead past the bar; 'men's' is to the right past the pool tables.
comment: This is a very laid-back, non-judgemental bar; anyone should easily feel comfortable being themselves.

directions: After entering cafe, head to the rear. Go past the counter and past the benches on the left. Turn towards teh left and there is a door. Go through door to short hallway with access to two single locking bathrooms.

name: Carleton University
directions: 4th floor unicentre across from the GLBT centre.
comment: 3rd floor Loeb building in tower A

name: Starbucks at World Trade Center
directions: Street level, corner of SW 2nd and Taylor
comment: It's a single-room locked bathroom.  I believe you have to ask the barristas for the key.  They are pretty friendly, though, so you may not have to buy anything.

name: Marriott Hotel
directions: Front lobby, in hallway towards Starbucks, just past the front desk. (Not the ones you have to go down stairs for - those are multistall.)

name: The Coup
comment: Vegetarian restaurant, cocktails, desserts. Historically gay part of town.

name: Book Barn Downtown
directions: Facilities are located just after Drama, just before Romance, and directly across from the VHS tapes.
comment: Open 9am to 9pm every day except for Thanksgiving and Christmas. 20+ lb. English Sumo Tabby on premises.

name: The Roasterie
comment: Good coffee

name: Zen West
directions: Back of the bar, through the marked door.  2 genderfree bathrooms on the other side of the door.
comment: Good food, nonsmoking through the whole restaurant

name: Cashion's Eat Place
comment: Awesome food.  But don't expect to use the bathroom unless you're eating here.

name: Mokabe's
directions: Walk all the way back, up the ramp and bathrooms are right there.
comment: Very friendly queer place on south grand, great  food and coffee.

name: UVA - New Cabell Hall
street: Jefferson Park Avenue (University of Virginia campus)
directions: 2nd Floor, East Wing
comment: Cabell is open 24/7

name: Brewed Awakenings
directions: Building is on the rotary at the South County Commons. If you park to the right of/behind the storefront, there's a side door which is RIGHT next to the bathrooms!
comment: Open late - 10pm.

name: Clocktower Brew Pub
directions: Main floor.

name: Cafe Sutra
directions: In the middle of the store; you have to ask for the key at the register (but sometimes the last person didn't close it all the way and you can just sneak in).

name: Tea Lounge
directions: All the way in the back
comment: I've never had a problem running in there to pee.  The Blue Haze tea is wonderful, though!

name: Le Cagibi
comment: This is one of my favourite cafe's in Montreal - the fact that their bathrooms are genderfree just makes me like them even more.  Staff is very queer friendly.

name: Café Dépôt
directions: Adjacent fo the counter. Two single-stall, unlocked washrooms, labelled gender-neutral.
comment: Café sharing space with a sushi bar. Corner of De Maisonneuve and Mackay, adjacent to Concordia University. Guy-Concordia metro station.

name: Le Frigo Vert
directions: In the sitting area in the rear of the store
comment: In Concordia University's vegan/organic food co-op. On rue Mackay north of de Maisonneuve, just northwest of Concordia's Hall Building (Guy-Concordia metro station).

name: Portland State University
directions: in Smith center on the Mezanine floor (between 2 & 3).  ther are two lockable rooms back-to-back.
comment: school hours.

name: katy mills
directions: unisex ADA accesible restroom available near the food court area
comment: no key required, walk right in do your thing.

name: arizona mills mall
directions: located near food court
comment: *family restroom*must have child for access*security(is watching)will buzz you in
